{"session_id": 49, "bill_id": 15744, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 207, "bill_title": "require orientation for school board members.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Governor", "School Board", "School District"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-09T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen22sb0207a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-09T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen22sb0207a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-09T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen22sb0207a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 15744, "bill_version_id": 87005, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2000-01-25T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require orientation for school board members. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 13-8 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any school board member elected after July 1, 2000, pursuant to chapter 13-7 shall successfully complete an orientation course. The orientation shall be completed within twelve months after the school board member has been elected and qualified. Each school board member shall receive basic orientation to local board policies and procedures, school district goals and priorities, state education laws and administrative rules, and relevant legal obligations, with special emphasis on statutory provisions related to academic content standards, assessment, and governing South Dakota school districts. The orientation, which may be delivered by any available technology, may not exceed six hours in length. 500 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from exi